Grupo Gigante SAB said it made an
offer last week to buy the 50 percent of Office Depot de Mexico
it doesnâ€™t already own from  Office Depot Inc. (ODP)   The company offered to pay 8.78 billion pesos ($689
million) for the stake, according to a filing with the Mexican
stock exchange.  Office Depot agreed to buy  OfficeMax Inc. (OMX)  for $1.17
billion, according to a statement yesterday. The company has
been exploring options since Starboard Value LP became its
largest shareholder in September.  Office Depot shares fell 4.8 percent to $3.98 today.
Gigante shares were unchanged today at 27 pesos.  To contact the reporters on this story:
